Local setup:
1. Download and install Django properly, follow the insturction on:
   https://www.djangoproject.com/download/ and
   https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/topics/install/

2. Get MySQL database running:
   Install MySQLdb

   Troubleshooting:
   - After MySQLdb is downloaded, if running "python setup.py build" gives you error
     regarding to "setuptools", that means you need to install it.
     More details on http://pypi.python.org/pypi/setuptools
     After download it, run the egg file. Ex: sh setuptools-0.6c11-py2.7.egg

   - After MySQLdb is downloaded, if running "python setup.py build" gives you error
     regarding to "mysql_config", you might have to make sure that mysql_config.path
     is the correct path where mysql_config is located in setup_posix.py file.

   - After MySQLdb is downloaded, if running "python setup.py build" gives you error
     regarding to missing gcc-4.2, that means you need to install it, it should be  
     included in Xcode.
